definitions.definition: Wealthy : having a lot of money and possessions .
Having an intense fatty or sugary flavour .
examples: a rich dish; rich cream or soup; rich pastry
a rich treasury; a rich entertainment; a rich crop
rich in fiber; rich in traditions

definitions.definition: Yielding large returns; productive or fertile ; fruitful .
examples: rich soil or land; a rich mine

definitions.definition: Composed of valuable or costly materials or ingredients; procured at great outlay; highly valued; precious; sumptuous; costly.
examples: a rich endowment; a rich dress; rich silk or fur; rich presents
The scene was a rich one.

definitions.definition: Ridiculous , absurd , outrageous , preposterous , especially in a galling , hypocritical , or brazen way.
Elaborate , having complex formatting , multimedia , or depth of interaction .
Of a solute-solvent solution: not weak (not diluted); of strong concentration.
examples: mixed up a batch that was quite rich

subdefinitions.definition: Of a fuel-air mixture: having more fuel (thus less air ) than is necessary to burn all of the fuel ; less air- or oxygen - rich than necessary for a stoichiometric reaction .

definitions.definition: Trading at a price level which is high relative to historical trends, a similar asset, or (for derivatives ) a theoretical value.
examples: The ETF is trading rich to NAV right now; we can arb this by selling the ETF and buying the underlying constituents.
